The victims were shot in Katilumla Village in Lusikisiki, Eastern Cape, on Thursday, 13 January at about 8.15pm.  “We are not used to guns so when I heard the shots, I just ran. I didn’t look back,” he said. He said he got into a taxi and was told by other passengers that the victims were two zangoma who were in the area to work. Police spokesman Sergeant Kaya Matola-Mvanyashe said on arrival at the scene, cops found two victims dead with gunshot wounds to their upper bodies. After a short while, the witness heard four gunshots.  The motive for the killing is unknown. No arrests have been made yet.